  "title": "LANDSCAPE ARCHITECT",
  "description": "<p><br /><br /></p><p><br /><br /></p><p><u><strong>Job Description </strong></u></p><p>1. General project work in all phases from concept up to detailedconstruction drawings, preparation of documentation and any otherproject materials under supervision of a team leader. </p><p>2. Monitor work progress to ensure project development is according todesign and time schedules. </p><p>3. Prepare and communicate design intent by computer generated orhand drawings within or outside office. </p><p>4. Liaison with clients, consultants, contractors and suppliers. </p><p>5. Attend project / technical / consultant and / or other co-ordinationmeetings. </p><p>6. Supervise, guide and advise Landscape Technicians working on theproject. </p><p>7. Any other duties that may be assigned from time to time by the teamleader.</p><p></p><p><u><strong>Job Requirements</strong></u> </p><p><br />1. A motivated and hardworking individual with good attitude who is ableto work independently as well as collaboratively in a team. </p><p>2. Individual with excellence in design and willingness to work hard andtakes initiative to complete given tasks thoroughly and efficiently. </p><p>3. Excellent academic performance as demonstrated by awards, forexample, Dean’s List, Prizes, Commendations. </p><p>4. Proficiency in AutoCAD / Vectorworks, SketchUp, Lumion, Photoshop,Microsoft Office and any other computer-aided drafting and designsoftware. </p><p>5. Good hand drawing skill and sketching ability. </p><p>6. Evidence of English language proficiency, both written and spoken. </p><p>7. Bachelor’s degree from a recognized Landscape Architecture programand University</p><p></p><p><br /></p>",
